# Today's Cybersecurity Analyst

## Overview
Cybersecurity analysts are responsible for protecting CIA of information in general and/or organizations . This requires a commitment to a 'defense-in-depth approach', using multipe overlapping security controls to achieve this goal. It also requires a strong understanding of the attack surface of an organization. allowing their organization to develop control sets capable of preventing and mitigating threats. This writeup will cover how to assess security threats, determine risk to CIA and the tools used to secure networks/endpoints then evaluate the effectivceness of those tools.

